This paper discusses a modification of conformal predictors, which are commonly used in machine learning and statistics. The paper focuses on two computationally efficient versions of conformal predictive systems, which are relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), statistics (cs.ST), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and social and information networks (cs.SI).
